sentences: In the latter half of the 1940s, he played with Dexter Gordon, Charlie Parker, and Ella Fitzgerald; in 1950 he and Oscar Peterson recorded duets, and he also played with Peterson and Charlie Smith as a trio.

Upon his return to America, he toured with Woody Herman in 1958 and with Al Cohn/Zoot Sims betweeb 1959 and 1960.

A prolific studio musician, he played with Duke Ellington in 1964 and with the Kenny Burrell Trio, Coleman Hawkins, Lee Konitz, Roy Eldridge, Michel Legrand, Milt Buckner, Jay McShann and Quincy Jones in the 1960s and 1970s.
From 1967 to 1970, he taught at the Berklee College of Music.
